I think the parents are making the right decision, and that the nay-sayers
should mind their own business.

The medical consensus for people with her condition seems to be
unanimous that she will never, ever improve.  Her parents now have
a lifetime job of taking care of her, every moment of every day.  The
girl is not going to have the slightest understanding of what is going
on, or the implications of the decisions her parents make.  If
continuing with these medical procedures makes it easier for her parents
to care for her, with no other known downsides, then why the heck would
any rational person speak against it?

- Rich

